ATTENTION ALL BULLDOGS AND LADY BULLDOGS:

As the 2020-2021 school year approaches, I wanted to pass along some information you will need for the start of the school year.

First, PHYSICALS. I am attaching a letter that explains about physicals for the upcoming year.

Second, ONLINE UIL FORMS AND EMERGENCY INFORMATION. The second attachment explains how to complete those things.

EVERYONE GRADES 7-12 MUST COMPLETE BOTH OF THESE ITEMS BEFORE YOU CAN PRACTICE OR PARTICIPATE IN ANY UIL EVENT.

If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Coach Zander at clint.zander@bosquevilleisd.org.

post_text: Attention Bulldogs and Lady Bulldogs, we will be resuming our Summer Strength and Conditioning and Sports Specific Training on Monday, July 13th. Attached is a calendar for the month of July. Please note that we will be adhering to all UIL guidelines and CDC recommendations. In those UIL guidelines is a requirement for all participants to wear a mask or cloth face covering of some sort. Please note that you will not be able to enter the workout area, or participate in workouts unless you have some kind of mask covering your nose and mouth. If you have any questions, please contact Coach Zander at clint.zander@bosquevilleisd.org.

Don’t forget, Summer Comditioning/Sports Soecific training begins tomorrow, June 8.
At this time, we are limiting these workouts to incoming HS age students only. Depending on how things go, and our overall numbers, we may open workouts up to JH students in the future.

HS Girls - 9:00am - field house

HS Boys - 10:00am or 5:30pm - field house.

DO NOT FORGET TO BRING HOUR OWN LABELED WATER BOTTLE. WE ARE NOT ALLOWED TO SUPPLY ANY WATER, AND THERE WILL BE NO ACCESS TO WATER FOUNTAINS.

Can’t wait to see everyone tomorrow.

post_text: Today’s news about the closing of schools, and the UIL cancellation of all spring activities hurts. I want to thank our senior athletes for all they have given to Bosqueville. You will be missed. You have done a great job of leading by example. Thank you for your countless hours of work. Words can’t really express what we are all feeling at this time. Hopefully you have learned some life lessons along the way that will help you deal with this, and other hurdles you face down the road of life. Once again, thank you, and we love you.

post_text:
Athletic Physicals for 2019-2020 School Year

If your child, or a child you know, that is currently in 6th-11th grade wants to participate in athletics next school year (2019-2020), the must have a physical prior to participating. Each student must have a physical each year they participate. The doctors at Southwest Sports Medicine will be giving physicals for our students on Saturday, May 4th at 12:00 noon. We will meet at the school at 11:30, and the students will be transported to MCC by bus. Physicals are $10 each. Each student must have the medical history portion of the physical filled out and signed by the parent/guardian prior to attending the physical day. Forms can be picked up from our trainer, Nic Lyon, or any coach. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact me at clint.zander@bosquevilleisd.org.

post_text:
Sub-Varsity Football Update

Itasca is limited with the number of kids they have due to some injuries and recent illnesses. They are going to shuffle their kids and make it to where both of our JH groups get to play tonight.
With that being said, we are going to play 3 quarters with our 7th grade group, and 3 quarters with our 8th grade group. That means the game times may be a little earlier than normal.
I wish I could be more definite, but we are doing our best to try to get all the kids an opportunity to play tonight.
The JV game will be regular length. It will probably just start earlier than normal.

post_text: Proud of my coaches and especially Coach Montez for organizing two great track meets this week. Monday we had over 430 JH kids at the meet and were done by 9:50. Tonight we had almost 300 HS kids and pulled off another great meet. With the heavy rains last night, it wasn’t perfect conditions, but we got all field events in successfully. It takes a bunch of great coaches and hard workers to pull that off. Thankful they are all on my team.

post_text:
Yesterday we hosted our 14th consecutive power lifting meet. Once again, everything went great. These events can not run smoothly without a tremendous amount of help.
Special thanks to Coach Mike Finnell for planning and organizing a great meet.
Special thanks to all of the following people/groups:
Our JH athletes, who had the gym set up for the meet in an hour and a half.
Our volunteer table workers who kept everything organized and moving along.
Our high school boys for being there to help spot and load the bars all day
The athletic booster club for running a great concession stand all day
And especially the coaching staff who spent all day working, and putting up with me when I get a little stressed and on edge.

Our meet is consistently one of the, if not the best meets in the state each year. This would not be possible without each and everyone chipping in to help.

Thank you,

Coach Zander

ATHLETIC PHYSICALS

Athletic physicals will be offered on Tuesday, May 16, 2017 at 5:30pm, in the old gym. Physicals will be performed by the doctors from Southwest Sports Medicine & Orthopedics. Physicals will cost $15.00 cash. Each student/athlete that plans on participating in a sport for the 2017-2018 school year, must have a new physical, dated after May 1st, 2017. We encourage students to take advantage of this opportunity to get their annual physical. Students will not be allowed to participate in any practices or games until they have a current physical on file.
